From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: ASK2 maintainers <ask2@vyos-ls1046a-build.local>
Date: Wed, 14 May 2026 18:10:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] fman_pcd: cc: real fman_pcd_cc_tree_create/destroy bodies
 (PR14c-body-1)

PR14c-body-1 of the ASK2 v1.0 PR14 series.  Replaces the PR14c-prep
-EOPNOTSUPP stubs for fman_pcd_cc_tree_create() and
fman_pcd_cc_tree_destroy() with real MURAM-resident tree-group-table
allocation per LS1046A RM 8.7.4.1.

The remaining four stubs (fman_pcd_cc_node_create, _add_key,
_modify_next_action, _destroy) stay -EOPNOTSUPP until PR14c-body-2..-4
land them.

This is a RE-ROLL of the original PR14c-body-1 patch (workspace SHA
3b791d1) which had a hunk header @@ -1,77 +1,242 @@ expecting a
77-line fman_pcd_cc.c baseline that never existed in this repo.  See
plans/PATCH-STACK-FORENSIC-2026-05-14.md for the full forensic.

Functional content is preserved verbatim from the original design memo:
- struct fman_pcd_cc_tree private to this TU.
- 256-byte fixed group table (16 entries x 16 bytes) per RM 8.7.4.1 P2.
- Dual-API MURAM: fman_pcd_muram_alloc/free for budget, then
  fman_muram_offset_to_vbase for the CPU iomem pointer.
- pcd->lock (mutex) serialises tree lifecycle on pcd->cc_trees.
- tree->lifecycle_lock (mutex) declared now, populated in PR14c-body-2.
- WARN_ON(!list_empty(&tree->nodes)) leak detection at destroy.

Build: zero-warning ARM64 cross-build on Cobalt 100.
Cross-ref: SDK fm_cc.c:6470-6483 CcTreeBuild + DeleteTree.

Signed-off-by: ASK2 maintainers <ask2@vyos-ls1046a-build.local>
---
